Pre-Game Insights: Guyana are the favorites based on home advantage.
Suriname’s away form doesn’t seem impressive, however, they will take confidence from their superior head-to-head record (13 against 5 wins).
Miscellaneous Highlights: Guyana have won their last five matches at home in all competitions.
Suriname have won once and lost four times in their last five matches on the road.
Others: Guyana vs Suriname will face off against each other for the 22nd time.
The top two finishers will advance to the quarterfinals while the fourth and fifth-placed teams will qualify for the Gold Cup preliminaries.
